<br>
In most situations monks ALREADY tank better than we do at high levels.  I thought it was only uber monks with north ToV and luclin uber mob gear.  Nope.  The cleric that typically heals for my grind group has indicated to me that he's now healing our L60 monks less than he heals me, a 60 warrior, in almost any single group situation.  That's because of a combination of the stupid AC cap and monks great block ability.  since they also kick out considerably more dmg, the monk is clearly a better choice.  Monks are even tanking a lot of raid mobs now.  <br>
<br>
Reality check - sk's and paladins tank almost as well as warriors NOW in almost every situation.  They get armor with just as good of an AC, unlike earlier days when warrior gear consistently had more AC, they do almost as much dmg thanks to amazing ratio weapons, and they hold aggro better.  They're already a better choice than a warrior in many situations.  To think they need more upgrades is ludicrous.<br>
<br>
The warrior class is already broken.  We're already the forgotten bastard child of Verant.  We can't solo for anything.  Our value in a group is dubious at best and if it's a group that mainly wants exp, we downright stink.  Our raid job can often be done by other classes now.  Our specialty of main tank, for which we gave up EVERYTHING else, is now matched or nearly matched by several other classes while we got none of their abilities to compensate.  We don't have a role.  Period.  As Furor said awhile back in the state of the warriors post, &quot;put a skirt on Sally...&quot; and &quot;i see dead weight&quot;.  60 levels and a bunch of AA's later, my main class is a joke.  <br>
