That's about as apples to apples a comparison as I can make.  You may not outdamage us, but you will be a lot closer than you should be.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> It stands as fact now that at the end game a duel weilding warrior can taunt BETTER then a SK using two agro weapons.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
I don't even have a clue what you could possibly base that statement on.  If you are actually trying to argue that an SK can't out agro a warrior at ANY level of the game from the time you get spells, you have exactly zero credibility.  Let's put this into perspective.  Ruling out the DC you get at level 9 (still a decent taunt), you get clinging darkness at 15 &amp; SV at 39; all for the cost of a few plat.  Meanwhile, most warriors have to wait until 50+ for any decent agro generating weapon at the cost of thousands of plat at least.  FFS, you can cast your spells AT ANY TIME, while we have to pray to the streaky RNG for a proc.  There should be no question to anyone with an IQ above room temperature who out taunts who.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I have a hella time taunting off of a warrior duel weilding a BoC and a SoD, I am sure once the Cursed starts coughing up bloodfrenzies my chance at ever getting agro is over.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Please correct me if I am wrong, but<br>
<br>
Enraging Blow = +500 hate<br>
Shadow Vortex = +1100 hate (this is from your own boards)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> As of right now a warrior using the BoC and SoD taunt weapons keeps the agro 90% of the time over me, this will go to 95% or more when the warrior replaces that SoD with a Bloodfrenzie. And that is me, the Knight of Hate using Shadow Vortex and Clinging darkness chain casts and taunting whenever the mob is not on me and the button is active and weilding the ultimate in proccing agro weapons a SK can use<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
The argument you are making here is (putting it kindly) meaningless.  WTF is a warrior doing wielding hate generating weaps if you are supposed to have agro; or rather, why are you trying to take agro from that warrior?  In any situation where you are supposed to be MA, that warrior WILL be bagging those weaps in favor of something more damaging and/or less taunting.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So you warriors can dish more melee damage then us<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
We should.  Sorry, but you don't get to tank as well as a non-defensive warrior, do damage as well as a warrior AND get a slew of great utility spells.  That's not balance, that's &quot;I want to be a warrior with some very usefull necro spells.&quot;<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> at the end game you can taunt better then us<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
No.  Also, this applies to about 1% of the warriors currently playing, what about the other 99%?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> and you own us in the tanking department.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Correct, on the 10% of encounters that require defensive.  In fact, we SHOULD be out tanking you on no less than 100% of encounters.  That is our JOB.  It's is all we have.  To complain about this is like complaining about clerics healing better than other wis casters.  Hello? what do we exist for if not to take damage?<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> so we can invis and have some self buffs, Kunark armor + really brought our utility close to yours with BP's that cast gather shodows, heals, strength buffs and other stuff on armour.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Please compare the cost of your spells to the cost of warrior invis items.  Let's not forget the chances of me even obtaining a pair of cobalt legs or chardok BP is somewhere between fat chance &amp; none.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Even IF we were able to tank as well as warriors then what is so bloody unbalancing about that?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Please read my above statement asking why we would even need to exist.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Trust in the fact we will NEVER tank as well as you<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
You already do in any situation that does not require defensive.  Lets just make a list of those:<br>
<br>
EVERYTHING in Kunark<br>
EVERYTHING up to &amp; including any slowable named in the planes<br>
EVERYTHING up to &amp; including Vind in Kael<br>
All non named in HoT/WToV (everything but possibly Doz in HoT)<br>
EVERYTHING except possibly Rumblecrush &amp; Doomshade in UP<br>
<br>
Hmm, I see a lot of &quot;everythings&quot; up there, and I am sure there is a lot missing.<br>
<br>
Let's just boil it down to the state of the warrior in EQ today.  Any raid leader would be a fool to NOT use a knight on anything that does not require defensive simply because of the HUGE benefits of good agro control.  That leaves warriors to tank the remaining 10% of content that requires defensive.  Also, these encounters are continually shrinking thanks to endless mana CH chains (a hand full of clerics + mod rod 2 + torpor + FT/mana song/c3), and the increasing abundance of all/all +HP items (the warrior HP advantage as a percentage of total shrinks).<br>
<br>
So don't come here bitching about how bad knights have it.  Once apon a time knights were the red headed step child of EQ, but no longer.  The only reason warriors still get the MA job is because of old conceptions &amp; habit.  Smart raid leaders will know to pick knights when defensive is not needed (increasingly most of the time).  Smart group leaders will know to pick monks for their far superior DPS &amp; greater damage avoidance with no loss to mitigation (thx AC cap). <p><br><font size=2>
