<br>
You find the 1 best tank in your guild (boss mobs)/group (XP).<br>
<br>
Every other tank doesn't really matter(1).<br>
<br>
If a Pal or SK becomes close to Warrior tanking, you are worthless.<br>
<br>
If not, the SK or Pal feels worthless.<br>
<br>
Because one of there most important abilities, the ability to tank, has been nearly completely nullified.<br>
<br>
Look, this shield idea really is cool.  BUT<br>
<br>
To clean up this arms race, there needs to be a way for more than 1 player to contribute to tankage.<br>
<br>
What if warriors, Pal, and SK got a 5% chance to intercept hits from the mob they have targetted?<br>
<br>
Yes, it would require alot of rebalancing at the high end.  With 20 warriors on a mob, hits would be effectively randomly distributed -- only 35% of attacks by boss mobs would actually hit the main tank, the rest would be intercepted by some other warriors body.  And the standard deviation on that 35% would be pretty low.<br>
<br>
It could also scale with mob difficulty somehow -- giving a higher chance in XP groups than on raids, making it a reason to have 2 tanks in an XP group *gasp*.(2)<br>
<br>
(1) Yes, sometimes you need 2 or 4 tanks.  These are few and far between.  And usually this is on a large raid.<br>
<br>
(2)<br>
CHANCE_TO_INTERCEPT = (PLAYER_DEX+PLAYER_AGI) * PLAYER_AC / (ATTACKER_ATK * 500) %?<br>
<br>
That would give about 10% with max dex/agi, and AC=ATK.  On weaker stuff (say, ubertank fully buffed on a L 45), your chance would go up to 20 to 30%.  And on raid mobs, it would probably drop to 5 to 8%<br>
<br>
Apologies for tangenting.<br>
