OK so you admit with similar weapons we will not outdamage you. If you imagine with melee alone we will come close to the damage of those two duel weild weapons you are mistaken. We were supposed to be about 85% of your melee damage, we are closer to 70%. Parse those, by all means.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Ruling out the DC you get at level 9 (still a decent taunt) <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
You just proved you know nothing about the SK spells as they currently stand. DC does NO agro now, the spell is completely worthless now. It is useful from levels 9-15 as a dd/dot for damage.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Please correct me if I am wrong, but<br>
<br>
Enraging Blow = +500 hate<br>
Shadow Vortex = +1100 hate (this is from your own boards)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yes, you are wrong. Where did you read that? please link to the post.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> The argument you are making here is (putting it kindly) meaningless. WTF is a warrior doing wielding hate generating weaps if you are supposed to have agro; or rather, why are you trying to take agro from that warrior? In any situation where you are supposed to be MA, that warrior WILL be bagging those weaps in favor of something more damaging and/or less taunting.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
OK the warrior is duel weilding hate generating weapons because he is MT. I am attempting to steal the agro because I am /GASP! Testing our nerfed agro generation capacity! The test was on mostly trash in PoG while we were clearing for Tuna, I would never try to steal the agro on anything meaningful because I would be lizard paste if I got it. The only thing I was trying to make you aware of is that at the end game warrior agro generation is huge. Maybe a pally can own you in agro but a SK no longer can. Warriors always spout off on how great we can taunt and how if we could tank as well as them they would be useless, well it is not exactly true we can taunt that great compared to your class at te END GAME.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 So you warriors can dish more melee damage then us<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
We should. Sorry, but you don't get to tank as well as a non-defensive warrior, do damage as well as a warrior AND get a slew of great utility spells. That's not balance, that's &quot;I want to be a warrior with some very usefull necro spells.&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yeah agreed. I never said I wanted to do as much melee damage.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 at the end game you can taunt better then us<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
No. Also, this applies to about 1% of the warriors currently playing, what about the other 99%?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I am talking about the end game. I am not talking about hanging out in sebilis at leel 55 duel weilding lammy's man. When I am talking about these problems I am talking about high end EQ where the warriors are all weilding BoC/SoD or better. I am not talking about the trakanon/farming west wing level of the game. I am talking the Cursed/AoW/Emp/VT level of the game. It is really only then we SK's really get screwed and shown up. By all means I agree we own warriors at level 45 hanging out in the dreadlands killing spiders and stuff when it comes to taunt.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Hello? what do we exist for if not to take damage?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Correct you are tanks. And warriors are heralded as the best tanks in the game and are required on most end game fights. Let me ask you this, since tanking is your niche that warriors own and are best at what are SK's niche? Yep, we have none. Welcome to our existence.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Please compare the cost of your spells to the cost of warrior invis items. Let's not forget the chances of me even obtaining a pair of cobalt legs or chardok BP is somewhere between fat chance &amp; none.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Again, I am talking end game. If a cobalt BP and Cobalt leggings are out of your reach then you really have no idea of the game I am talking about. Trak and Venril were trivial almost 2 years ago and those pieces are easily affordable or farmable by the people I deal with day to day.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Quote:<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
 Even IF we were able to tank as well as warriors then what is so bloody unbalancing about that?<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
Please read my above statement asking why we would even need to exist<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
And I hope you see where I am comming from. In the end game warriors are basically caught up to us in every way and we have very little that is unique. It is not warriors fault, it is Verants. I dont want to tank as well as a warrior, I do believe that is your roll and you should be the masters at it. But what about us SK's? Where do we fit into the grand scheme of things? I dont want to tank as well as you but I want SOMETHING, and Verant does not have a clue what to do with us. As it stands right now even if we tanked as well as a warrior we most likely would still be inferior which is a joke Verant has played on us and they dont even realise it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Let's just boil it down to the state of the warrior in EQ today. Any raid leader would be a fool to NOT use a knight on anything that does not require defensive simply because of the HUGE benefits of good agro control<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Lots of fools abound then. I will bet ya 60,000pp that most end game Emp+ guilds out there use a warrior as main tank on both the trash and the named. The taunt is moot as I said once you hit the level of game I am at.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> So don't come here bitching about how bad knights have it. Once apon a time knights were the red headed step child of EQ, but no longer<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
No, they finally stuck us in a orphanage and hoped that we would not show up years later at their doorstep saying &quot;Dad, Mom, Why did you abandon me!&quot;<br>
<br>
************************************<br>
<br>
I dont have anything against warriors. I admit your class is not perfect and you have a single roll to protect for yourselves. Monks and their recent accension to god status screwed your class just as much as it did ours relatively speaking. I really hope Verant takes the time to fix your class and put warriors where they should be in the game. I just also hope that the warriors dont screw over the SK class on such posts as this by making us out to be some balanced and meaningful class that we are certainly not. Most people at the very end game will admit SK's get the shaft in class balance.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
